<HEADLINE>
FT  29 OCT 93 / Technology (Worth Watching): Turning the wheels on the car
thief
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANNA KOCHAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
To combat the growing trend of car theft, a new French device renders a
vehicle unable to be driven by disengaging the steering wheel from the
steering column, writes Anna Kochan. Anyone breaking into the car and
starting the engine finds the steering wheel turning without steering the
wheels.
The device, produced by Malvy Technology, can be fitted during assembly or
later at a cost of Ffr4,800 (Pounds 560). It consists of a sealed box
containing a series of mechanical locks which fit between the steering
column and the wheel. The key provides more than 100m combinations.
Malvy's system will become available in January. Insurance companies have
indicated they will lower premiums on cars equipped with the product. Malvy
Technology: France, 331 60192000.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
