<HEADLINE>
FT  29 OCT 93 / Company productivity growing
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A MAJORITY of top personnel managers say their companies' productivity is
growing and expect further increases in the next 12 months. A MORI poll of
181 delegates at the Institute of Personnel Management Conference found that
80 per cent reported productivity increases in the past year. Nearly half
said the improvement had been better than 3 per cent.
Some 60 per cent said their workforce had fallen in the past year: 15 per
cent of those by more than a tenth.
Most managers said their companies had improved cost-effectiveness,
profitability and business success, but at a price. Some 81 per cent of them
reported increased stress levels among staff and 61 per cent believed
employee morale had deteriorated.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
