May, I would feed my family,' he said.
He said he had no knowledge of the disappearance of antique furniture worth
Pounds 20,000 and of gym equipment from his company's offices.
It also emerged yesterday that the Salvation Army intends to seek summary
judgment against Mr Ford on December 8, and plans similar actions against
several other individuals.
After the examination, Mr Ford issued a statement. 'I have made it clear
today and all along that I did not in any way defraud the Salvation Army,'
he said.
</TEXT>
