FT  28 OCT 93 / International Company News: Flotation for new Canadian
timber group
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
FLETCHER Challenge Canada is putting most of its timber and logging
operations into a new company, TimberWest, and will then take it public in
December.
FCC, controlled by Fletcher Challenge of New Zealand, will retain 51 per
cent of the new company. Analysts estimate FCC will raise almost CDollars
100m (USDollars 76m) from the spin-offs.
TimberWest will own two big coastal wood products plants, 210,000 hectares
of private forest lands, crown licences from the Queen Charlotte Islands to
southern Vancouver Island, plus logging operations and Interior sawmills. It
will continue to supply fibre to FCC mills.
