FT  28 OCT 93 / International Company News: Canada Trustco profits up 11%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CANADA Trustco (CT), the country's biggest trust company, posted
third-quarter profit of CDollars 49m (USDollars 37m) or 36 cents a share, up
from CDollars 44m or 34 cents a share a year earlier. Nine months' earnings
were CDollars 121m or 90 cents a share, against CDollars 166m or CDollars
1.32 a share.
CT is almost fully owned by Imasco, the tobacco products, fast food and
retailing group, through CT Financial Services.
