FT  28 OCT 93 / International Company News: Newmont Mining tops expectations
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
NEWMONT Mining, the Denver-based gold company, exceeded market expectations
yesterday with third-quarter earnings boosted by the higher gold price and
an increase in production.
Newmont Gold, the company's 90 per cent-owned north American mining
subsidiary, reported net income of Dollars 41.7m, or 40 cents a share, up
from Dollars 23.7m or 23 cents the year before.
Sales rose from Dollars 143.5m to Dollars 170m as production at Newmont Gold
jumped by 10 per cent to 453,200 ounces. The results were also bouyed by the
gold price, which averaged Dollars 375 an ounce, up from Dollars 348.
Total sales were up by 15 per cent, to Dollars 178m. The parent company
reported net income of Dollars 25.7m or 32 cents, up from Dollars 18m or 27
cents.
