FT  28 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Deficit at Bullers reduced to Pounds 1.42m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Bullers, the giftware, fine art and decorative products group, incurred
losses of Pounds 1.42m over the 12 months to June 30.
The outcome - which came on turnover of Pounds 2.43m - compared with a
deficit of Pounds 8.22m for the previous 18 month period, restated for FRS
3, some Pounds 6.2m of which related to discontinued operations. Sales last
time amounted to Pounds 10.8m, including Pounds 5.68m from discontinued
activities.
Losses per share were reduced to 1.22p (12.49p).
Lord Eden is standing down as chairman of the group in favour of Mr David
Cunningham, chairman of Waterglade International.
