FT  28 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Glenchewton deficit deepens to Pounds
463,000 at midway
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LOSSES at Glenchewton, the toys, housewares and basketware group, widened
from Pounds 242,000 to Pounds 463,000 pre-tax for the six months to
end-June.
However, the previous deficit, which was adjusted to comply with FRS 3,
included litigation costs recovered amounting to Pounds 247,000.
Turnover of continuing operations rose from Pounds 6.42m to Pounds 7.3m. And
with sales weighted to the second half directors said they were confident
they would be able to report a 'healthy operating profit' for the second six
months.
Net interest payable declined to Pounds 49,000 (Pounds 174,000). Losses per
share increased to 2.09p (1.37p).
Sir Victor Garland, chairman, said the initial focus would be to improve and
optimise the efficiency and growth of the group's current operations.
