<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Hanson's restructuring of Beazer building
business in US
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
HANSON, the Anglo-US conglomerate, yesterday said it would restructure its
Beazer building business in the east coast of the US.
Hanson, which acquired Beazer in 1991, is splitting its east coast
operations into two units.
The first, to be called Spectrum Construction Group and headquartered at
Virginia Beach, will take over most of its construction and paving
activities. The companies consolidated into Spectrum have aggregate annual
revenues of Dollars 500m.
The second unit, Benchmark Materials Company, will take in all aggregate
operations including some asphalt paving 'where fully integrated with
aggregates.'
Benchmark - to be based in Raleigh, North Carolina - will have revenues of
Dollars 325m. It will supply about 50m tons of aggregates, 3m tons of
asphalt and related services to construction, railroad and agricultural
industries.
Mr John Wimberly, chairman and chief executive of Beazer USA, said the move
'will focus management and streamline Beazer's business on the East Coat. It
will also align our operations to better fit the markets they serve.'
</TEXT>
