<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Healthcare behind expansion at Shiloh
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GROWTH IN its healthcare operations helped Shiloh report profits before tax
more than doubled, from Pounds 201,000 to Pounds 490,000, for the half year
to October 2.
Sales rose 84 per cent to Pounds 13.4m.
The Lancashire-based group has expanded from its original textile spinning
activities and as well as heathcare also takes in protective clothing and
packaging businesses.
Mr Edmund Gartside, chairman, said that healthcare now represented 55 per
cent of group turnover and 71 per cent of profits.
Textiles had shown a 'modest improvement' he said and the initial signs of
recovery in the sector were apparent.
Packaging, on the other hand, was flat although some improvement was
expected in the second half.
The interim dividend goes up to 1p (0.875p), payable from earnings of 5.75p
(2.36p) per share.
</TEXT>
