<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Allied-Lyons opens Russian ice-cream plant
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Allied-Lyons, the drinks, food and retailing group, has celebrated the
topping out of a Dollars 30m (Pounds 19.8m) Baskin-Robbins ice-cream
manufacturing plant in Moscow.
The plant, when fully operational, will produce up to 8m gallons of
ice-cream a year for Baskin-Robbins' expanding chain of shops and kiosks in
Russia's main cities.
Since 1988, 12 stores and 50 kiosks have been opened in Moscow, St
Petersburg and Novgorod. Ice-cream supplied from the US is also being sold
in 10 hard currency stores in Moscow.
The ice-cream plant will employ 170 Russian staff.
