<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Guardian Group in talks to raise further
finance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GUARDIAN Group, the USM-quoted building and environmental services company
formerly known as Associated Energy Services, is in discussions to raise
further finance, said Mr John Broad, the chairman.
Its potential could only be realised if it acquired adequate funds both for
future growth and to deal with 'the remaining difficulties of the past', he
added.
At the same time the company announced pre-tax losses of Pounds 420,103 for
the seven months to June 30 1992. For all of 1991 there were losses of
Pounds 840,098. Mr Broad said he would inform shareholders of the results
for the year to June 30 1993 'at the earliest possible date.'
The company continued to survive only because of the support given by its
main shareholder, Guardian Foundations, he said.
The shares lost 1 1/4 p to 7 3/4 p.
Attributable losses came through at Pounds 388,345 (Pounds 1.26m), a rise
from the unaudited accounts because of a further loss relevant to Clevedon
Homes, audit fees, redundancy and reorganisation costs and inter-company
write-offs.
Losses per share were 0.36p (0.89p for 12 months).
