<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Queens Moat accounts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAGGIE URRY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE NEW management team at Queens Moat Houses, the hotel group which was
plunged into crisis talks with its bankers in March, is close to finalising
its accounts for 1992 and expects to post them to shareholders by the end of
next week.
The accounts will call for the annual meeting to be reconvened on November
29. The meeting has been adjourned since August awaiting the final figures.
Although they are still being worked on, the accounts could show negative
net assets compared with shareholders' funds of Pounds 1.3bn at the end of
1991. The group's debts exceed Pounds 1bn. The sharp reduction in asset
values reflects property write-downs, described by insiders as 'horrendous',
and retained losses.
The fall in asset values reaffirms speculation that the figures might have
been overstated in earlier balance sheets. The company's new directors have
already said they are considering taking action over the accounts.
As a result of the drop in asset value, the group has had to call an
extraordinary meeting because net assets total less than half the paid-up
share capital of Pounds 251.5m. The EGM will be held on November 22, but
will be adjourned and combined with the annual meeting.
</TEXT>
