FT  28 OCT 93 / Technology: Buzzwords - Software at Work
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GEOGRAPHICAL INFORMATION SYSTEMS use maps or locations on-screen. They match
other data, such as demographic or financial, to a map or other
representation of physical space.
DATA CAPTURE, sometimes known as data take-on, presents specific
difficulties for a GIS. Data cleansing - the process of resolving
discrepancies or omissions in data - is a large part of the task. Sheffield
reports that it found relatively few omissions.
